A video game featuring Kournikova's licensed appearance, titled Anna Kournikova&apos;s Smash Court Tennis, was developed by Namco and released for the PlayStation in Japan and Europe in November 1998.
A computer virus named after her arose on 12 February 2001 and infected computers worldwide through internet mail.
