In the Attic‚ÄìIonic dialect of Ancient Greek, long alpha fronted to (eta). In Ionic, the shift took place in all positions. In Attic, the shift did not take place after epsilon, iota, and rho (Œµ, Œπ, œÅ; e, i, r). In Doric and Aeolic, long alpha is preserved in all positions.
